tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE experimental_data (
  experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_name VARCHAR(255),
  experiment_date DATE,
  experiment_results TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE experimental_data (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_name VARCHAR(255),
  experiment_date DATE,
  data_type VARCHAR(50),
  data_value FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE machine_learning_analysis (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  data_id INT,
  algorithm_used VARCHAR(255),
  accuracy FLOAT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE experimental_data (
    experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_name VARCHAR(50),
    experiment_date DATE,
    data_source TEXT,
    sample_size INT
);

CREATE TABLE biological_data (
    data_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT REFERENCES experimental_data(experiment_id),
    species VARCHAR(50),
    genotype VARCHAR(50),
    phenotype VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE ml_analysis (
    analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id INT REFERENCES experimental_data(experiment_id),
    analysis_method VARCHAR(50),
    accuracy FLOAT,
    model_details TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE measurements (
  measurement_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_id INT,
  subject_id INT,
  measurement_date TIMESTAMP,
  result DECIMAL(10,2)
);

CREATE TABLE experiment_data (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
experiment_name VARCHAR(255),
sample_name VARCHAR(255),
measurement_1 FLOAT,
measurement_2 FLOAT);

CREATE TABLE metadata (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
experiment_id INT,
experiment_date DATE,
researcher_name VARCHAR(255));

CREATE TABLE machine_learning_results (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
experiment_id INT,
model_name VARCHAR(255),
accuracy FLOAT,
precision FLOAT,
recall FLOAT);

CREATE TABLE machine_learning_models (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
model_name VARCHAR(255),
algorithm_used VARCHAR(255),
hyperparameters JSON);

CREATE TABLE research_team (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
researcher_id INT,
researcher_name VARCHAR(255),
research_area VARCHAR(255),
affiliation VARCHAR(255)}
